The paper deals with action segmentation in videos, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel domain adaptation technique, which involves self-supervised learning, and uses deep learning models, which are common in machine learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also evaluates its proposed method on three benchmark datasets, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO).
